    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presented is a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in pristine condition. This example features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, boasting individual throttle bodies and a 7,900 RPM redline. Mechanically, it is beyond reproach: the VANOS system has been professionally overhauled, and the rod bearings have been replaced with treated shells for long-term reliability. The rear subframe has undergone proactive reinforcement to ensure structural integrity under high lateral loads. Power is managed via a crisp 6-speed Getrag manual transmission and a variable M differential lock. The suspension maintains factory-correct kinematics with refreshed bushings and dampers throughout. Finished in its original paint with deep luster and zero blemishes, this is a turn-key investment for the discerning purist seeking the zenith of the E46 chassis.",
